% ===================== 5. INITIAL PROBLEM =====================
\section{Initial Problem}

The original programming method described in the manual did not work because:

\begin{problembox}{Root Causes}
\begin{itemize}
  \item ESP32 bootloader rejected serial data
  \item TinyFPGA programmer dependencies were missing
  \item Module errors occurred
  \item Programming flow was unclear
\end{itemize}
\end{problembox}

Initially attempted:
\begin{codebox}
\begin{lstlisting}
tinyfpga-programmer-gui.py
\end{lstlisting}
\end{codebox}

Result:
\begin{codebox}
\begin{lstlisting}
ModuleNotFoundError: tinyfpgab
\end{lstlisting}
\end{codebox}

% ===================== 6. SOLUTION =====================
\section{Solution}

Instead of the system Python interpreter, use the project's virtual environment.

\begin{successbox}{Correct Command}
\begin{lstlisting}[language=bash]
cd ~/qorc-sdk/TinyFPGA-Programmer-Application

sudo ./venv/bin/python \
tinyfpga-programmer-gui.py \
--port /dev/ttyACM0 \
--appfpga <bitstream.bin> \
--mode fpga
\end{lstlisting}
\end{successbox}

This successfully programs the FPGA.

