% ===================== ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS =====================
\section{Root Cause Analysis}

The problem is unlikely to be Raspberry Pi Imager. Evidence indicates the SD card disconnects during the final synchronization stage.

\begin{warnbox}{Most Probable Causes}
\begin{enumerate}
  \item Faulty USB SD card reader
  \item Poor contact between SD card and reader
  \item Defective or counterfeit microSD card
  \item Unstable USB connection
  \item USB controller temporarily disconnecting the reader
\end{enumerate}
\end{warnbox}

\begin{infobox}{Interpretation}
The kernel log strongly indicates a \textbf{hardware communication failure} rather than a software configuration issue.
\end{infobox}

