% ===================== PROJECT OVERVIEW =====================
\section{Project Overview}

The objective is to program an FPGA board that uses an onboard \textbf{ESP32} as the programming interface. The FPGA bitstream, generated from Verilog code, is uploaded to the FPGA through the ESP32 bootloader over a USB serial connection.

\begin{infobox}{Two Environments Attempted}
\begin{enumerate}
  \item Android (Termux + PlatformIO)
  \item Ubuntu Linux (PlatformIO)
\end{enumerate}
The goal was to compile the firmware successfully and upload it to the ESP32 so that it could program the FPGA.
\end{infobox}

% ===================== METHOD 1: ANDROID =====================
\section{Method 1: Android (Termux + PlatformIO)}

\subsection*{Objective}
Attempt to compile and upload the project entirely from an Android phone using Termux.

\subsection*{Environment}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Android
  \item Termux
  \item Python 3.13
  \item pip
  \item PlatformIO Core
  \item ESP32 target
\end{itemize}

\begin{codebox}
\begin{lstlisting}[language=bash]
python --version
pip --version
pio --version
\end{lstlisting}
\end{codebox}

\subsection*{Project Structure}
\begin{codebox}
\begin{lstlisting}
vaman_7segment/
|
|-- platformio.ini
|-- src/
|-- include/
|-- lib/
`-- ...
\end{lstlisting}
\end{codebox}

\subsection*{Build Attempt}
\begin{codebox}
\begin{lstlisting}[language=bash]
cd ~/vaman_7segment
pio run
pio run --target build
pio run -t compiledb
\end{lstlisting}
\end{codebox}

\subsection*{Error Encountered}
PlatformIO failed \textbf{before compilation} because pySerial attempted to enumerate serial ports.

\begin{problembox}{Import Error}
\begin{lstlisting}
ImportError:
Sorry: no implementation for your platform ('posix') available
\end{lstlisting}
PlatformIO internally imports \texttt{serial.tools.list\_ports}. Android is not officially supported for serial enumeration inside PlatformIO.
\end{problembox}

\begin{warnbox}{Consequence}
\begin{itemize}
  \item No compilation occurred.
  \item No firmware binary was generated.
  \item Upload was impossible.
\end{itemize}
\end{warnbox}

\subsection*{Root Cause}
PlatformIO Core assumes desktop Linux serial device naming (\texttt{/dev/ttyUSB*}, \texttt{/dev/ttyACM*}). Android Termux does not expose serial devices the same way, and pySerial cannot enumerate Android USB serial devices.

\begin{infobox}{Verdict}
This is a \textbf{PlatformIO compatibility limitation}, not a project issue.
\end{infobox}

\subsection*{Additional Investigation}
The ESP-IDF generated configuration file was inspected:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{@{}ll@{}}
\toprule
\rowcolor{lightbg}
\textbf{Setting} & \textbf{Value} \\
\midrule
Target & \texttt{CONFIG\_IDF\_TARGET="esp32"} \\
Console UART & \texttt{CONFIG\_ESP\_CONSOLE\_UART\_NUM=0} \\
Monitor Baud & 115200 \\
Flash Baud & 115200 \\
Flash Mode & DIO \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

These settings confirmed that the project configuration itself was valid.

